      <span class="section-tag">WHY MERCHANTS GET BANNED</span>
      <h2 class="section-headline">Stripe rarely warns you first. By the time you get flagged, it's too late.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Most DTC merchants find out their Stripe account is under review only when revenue drops to zero.
        By then, Stripe has already made up its mind — you've lost your payment processor with no recourse.
      </p>
      <p class="section-body">
        Account Guardian monitors the same signals Stripe uses to flag accounts — dispute rate, refund rate,
        chargeback rate, and revenue trends — and alerts you the moment something crosses a threshold.
        You get days or weeks of warning before Stripe acts.
      </p>
      <div class="genome-traits">
        <div class="trait">
